Most people only know how to kill termites.  But lets kill perception instead🤪
A Termite mound is giant, 👑 royal, crawling brain. The outside layer is a skin with passageways that allow the mound to breathe – like a lung. The organism’s stomach is the symbiotic fungus that sits in catacombs under the mound, digesting grasses delivered by termites. The mound’s “mouth” can be found in the hundreds of tunnels the termites construct through the surrounding landscape. Because they carry nutrients and rebuild the mound, the sterile workers resemble blood cells. The mound’s “immune system” is the soldiers, who rush to defend the space whenever it is invaded 💪💪💪

Love is one of the intangible wonders of the world, it unites us all regardless of background, culture size or shape. We can all be loved, give love and share our love with others. Love is something that has been expressed for thousands of years, and since its Valentine’s day I wanted to share a story about one of the world’s most ancient actions of love. Not talking about Valentine or Cupid, but the oldest archers of love; the San people of the Kalahari.
 When a young man has his eye on an eligible woman he makes a miniature bow and arrow, this is the love bow. When the time is right, and the young man is ready, he signals his intention to marry the lady of his choice by aiming and shooting the tiny arrow at the lady’s bum. Fortunately, the special ‘love bow’ he uses is small enough, and made to bounce off her gently. The girl then has to make a decision. If she loves him, she will pick up the arrow and place it on her heart – but if not, she will leave it lying on the dusty ground. Only a true hunter is worthy of love. A woman needs a hunter and the hunter needs a gatherer, and if the match is right they can aim for a future filled with love and sustainability. .

I think all people on the planet are born with a deep calling. To do something.
It’s not always easy to know what that something is, especially when society tries to trap you into a flow of thinking that you are just here to do a fucking job, get some followers, buy some things, get a house, find love, and get a family. 
Some of us are here to help mothers give birth to children, some are here to help us bury our dead, some of us are here to tell mothers and fathers that it’s going to be okay, some are here to help us talk about our problems, some are here to teach kids all the basics to be prepared for a life, some of us are here to evolve technology, culture or systems of rule. Some of us are here working the jobs that no one else wants, and although they are not often recognized, they are sometimes the ones who perhaps create the most flow in society. Some are here to lead, some are here to follow.
Some are here to create, bring lightness and fun to millions of starving hearts, whilst others are here to feed millions of starving stomachs. It’s not easy to know why we are here or what our purpose is, but if something is constantly burning your lips and setting your belly on fire then that is what you should be doing. ✌

Thank you 2018
This year has been a year of challenge, reveal, questions and wondering. Am I happy with my life the way it is? Do I do what I do because I want to do it? or is it just an old choice that grew into a feeling of having to do what I think I am expected to do? I have spent 10 years working hard to save indigenous people and conserve wildlife, but in the process, I forgot to take care of myself. The ecosystems I devoted my life to saving were thriving, whilst my own body was fighting to stay alive. I just wanted to show everyone all the successes to give people hope and inspiration, but there is no way of making a real difference if I don’t dare to share the shadows of my heart. I can’t do shit for others if I don’t start with the basics: Myself.
I have succeeded and failed.. I have built things and also seen some of them fall apart. I have been strong and free, but I have also felt weak and trapped. So thank you UNIVERSE for all the lessons and reveals. I will not enter the new year with a bunch of New year resolutions trying to change undesired habits/behaviors. I don’t like the idea that we have to stop something, its more about growing, and entering a new level of living. I want to share more, play more, I want to take care of myself, so I can better contribute to others. I want to roar the song of my soul. Be open and honest.. and hold myself as much as I love to hold others. I am a woman on Earth. Earth is a beautiful place, and sometimes a very confusing place. What do we want? What do we need?  we make the right decision? What if we fail? What if we succeed? what if we regret? is it too late? It’s never too late.
We all like to pretend that we know, but shit scared to tell others that we have no idea what we are doing. Maybe the answers will come if we allow ourselves to be a human being and not just a human doing. I wish everyone a beautiful new year full of all the things that feels close to your heart, and a bunch of courage to share with others what lives in that heart. I came to work with wildlife so I could finally realise my childhood dream of living like Pocahontas and being one with nature. Little did I know that the only thing I was sustaining was my African EGO and not the environment. I was still separate from Nature 🙈
By observing nature I started to notice that there is not a single animal that wakes up in the morning with a vision to make nature a better place, but by being who they are and doing what they are here to do, they automatically make nature a better place. There is not a single cheetah who wants to be a lion or a meerkat who dream about becoming a buffalo. Only people have that problem. 
In our world we are all trying to prove ourselves and become someone bigger or better. Women are trying to prove that women can do everything men can do, and in the process women are losing their own superpowers. Men are still trying to prove that they are strong, that they don’t cry and that they can do everything on their own.. and in the process they loose the opportunity to be their own free self publicly.  Kids are trying to be older and old people are trying to be younger. 
Animals do not diet, or trim their mane to look hotter, animals do not starve because they are unhappy or eat to fill empty spaces. A lioness does not need to walk next to a woman to feel like a strong lioness. You see, she already know that she is powerful, nurturing, fierce and strong. She knows she needs her pride of fellow lions to thrive, and every night they’ll stand together or apart and lift their heads towards the stars and roar the purpose of their heart. We are nature 📸: @asatallgard

When I first came to Namibia I was looking AFTER lions pretending to be Phocahontas. Then I realized that there are much larger conservation challenges out there, and that if we don’t do something and if we don’t get help from indigenous peoples who knows nature the best, we might not even have lions or wildlife left for the next generation to experience.. The lion population has decreased so much that we have to spend days looking FOR lions to be able to look OUT for the lions and their future. Poaching and human wildlife conflict is knocking on the door from the east, west, north and south. People will sometimes kill cheetahs if they perceive them as a threat to their livestock, even though cheetahs rarely take domesticated animals. Let’s expand the ecological conciousness and  become the change. A little share of gratitude: Two years ago I was fighting for my life 💪That’t what you get when you try to help people and nature so much that you forget to take care of yourself.. and you don’t listen when your body tries to talk to you. 
One year ago two Ju/‘hoansi San guys and I walked across Namibia👣It was an unforgettable journey. We experienced nature in all its forms, people and humanity in all it versatility, they discovered the ocean and tarred roads for the first time, and I discovered that nothing can make you happy its something you are. 
There was love, danger, long distances, food, frustration, anger, and no food, blisters, 🦁 roar, 🐘, and an ocean we could not drink. There was moments where I cried, moments where I questioned, moments of laughter, adventure and true authenticity.. we don’t just live in nature we are of nature. This year I was finally ready to grow into my full expression and let nature move into my body. To free ourselves from things that distract our minds from what really matters. We don't need much to live, we don't have to fit the expectations of anyone, we don't need to constantly prove ouRselves. We just need to stay honest in what we do, care less of other's opinions and realize that we are all just people wanting to receive and give love. If you live simple, nature provides you everything you need. So I challenge you to #TakeitOFF (your clothes, your make-up, your shoes, your hair tie, your ear-plugs, your insta filters or your work image and challenge our conformity. Post one #takeitoff image /video/and challenge at least 5 of your friends to shed a layer and maybe even donate some dollars to Nanofasa's San people www.nanofasa.com . The Movement is what you make out of it.
